abstract: Ukrainian Prime Min Arseniy P Yatsenyuk survives no-confidence vote after Opposition Bloc party abstains from proceedings; attempted ouster comes amid infighting and disappointment over failure of Yatsenyuk's pro-Western government to root out corruption.

headline.print_headline: Worlds Briefing | Europe; Ukraine: Premier Survives Challenge
headline.main: Ukraine’s Prime Minister, Arseniy Yatsenyuk, Survives No-Confidence Vote

snippet: Mr. Yatsenyuk faced wavering allies in the party of President Petro O. Poroshenko, who had called on him to resign.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Yatsenyuk faced wavering allies in the party of President Petro O. Poroshenko, who had called on him to resign.
